        aria-label="Block with the history of Barbara Oakley"
      )
        .container.page__container
          article.article.oakley__article
            h2.article__title.title
              | Barbara Oakley&rsquo;s story
            .article__main-text
              p.article__paragraph.text
                | From childhood, Barbara was not given mathematics. She
                | considered herself a&nbsp;complete humanist, and far from
                | being the smartest. In&nbsp;the army, she studied Russian
                | to&nbsp;get a&nbsp;raise, and so&nbsp;successfully that she
                | was promoted to&nbsp;commander. But for promotion, you had
                | to&nbsp;take math. And then Barbara came up&nbsp;with her own
                | approach to&nbsp;the exact sciences. It&nbsp;turned out that
                | if&nbsp;something is&nbsp;&laquo;badly given&raquo;
                | to&nbsp;you, your knowledge gained by&nbsp;labor is&nbsp;much
                | deeper than that of&nbsp;those to&nbsp;whom everything
                | is&nbsp;clear at&nbsp;first sight.
